<title type="html"><![CDATA[Hover over tray buttons don't show thumbnail]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=8019&amp;p=34468#p34468"><![CDATA[
Hello!<br />Until I used Win 8.1, if the tray wasn't full, (so the app buttons weren't grouped), if I hovered the mouse pointer over a button on the tray, I could see a thumbnail/miniature of the opened window, even if an app had multiple opened windows.<br />Now, with Windows 10, the situation is slightly different: If there is more than one window opened from the same app, when I hover the mouse pointer over a tray button, I see only the opened windows' list, although I see them side by side, as you can see on this picture:<br /><img src="https://www.dropbox.com/s/k14lkjzx8hzl1tm/Clipboard01.jpg?dl=0" alt="" /><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/k14lkjzx8hzl1tm/Clipboard01.jpg?dl=0" class="postlink">https://www.dropbox.com/s/k14lkjzx8hzl1tm/Clipboard01.jpg?dl=0</a><br />(I'm sorry, picture insertion didn't work, so I could share the picture only as a link.)<br />The miniature still shows up on buttons, which belong to apps that have only one opened window:<br /><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/s/lxvaou9rnqrwpi2/Clipboard02.jpg?dl=0" class="postlink">https://www.dropbox.com/s/lxvaou9rnqrwpi2/Clipboard02.jpg?dl=0</a><br />Does anyone know, how to get back that behavior I experienced with Win 8.1?<br />Thanks,<br />Gabor<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2762">FelixRaven</a> — Tue Oct 17, 2017 8:03 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
